'The Barber Paradox'‚Å†
Named after Bertrand Russell in 1901, it bamboozles the grey matter as follows!‚Å†
'The barber is the one who shaves all those, and those only, who do not shave themselves'!‚Å†
The question is, does the barber shave himself?‚Å†
And thus a contradiction appears.....the barber cannot shave himself as he only shaves those who do not shave themselves!  Thus if he shaves himself he ceases to be the barber!‚Å†
Conversely, if the barber does not shave himself then he fits into the group who would be shaved by the barber and thus as the barber, he can shave himself!...‚Å†
‚Å†
It may be too late to shave me from this but please shave yourselves!!‚Å†
With the warmest of delight‚Å†
Lady Penelope‚Å†
